children.text: The doorway has not been properly waterproofed as required by the BCA and the relevant Australian Standard AS 3740, which could allow water to leak into the frame and cause possible future damage.
Part 3.8.1.2 of the Building Code of Australia (NCC/BCA) - Wet Areas, states that;
‘Building elements in wet areas within a building must-
be waterproof or water resistant in accordance with Table 3.8.1.1; and
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3740 – Waterproofing of domestic wet areas states in section 3.9.1.2 Perimeter flashing at floor level openings that

‘A water stop that has a vertical leg finishing flush with the top of the finished floor level shall be installed at floor level openings. The water stop shall be waterproofed to the perimeter flashing’
The builder must install fully waterproofed waterstops to all of the wet area openings of this home as required by the NCC/BCA and the relevant Australian Standard AS 3740.
